post_text:
Guidelines for tonight’s football game.

- Visitor Gate (facing East by Tennis Courts) Restrooms Doors 16 & 17 at HS
- All people sitting in or standing along the Visitor Stands MUST use the East Gate.
- Priority Ticketing will be used for HOME Varsity FOOTBALL Games
- The opposing school’s AD will play a pivotal role in the distribution procedures of the opposing school’s allotment of tickets.
- Max is 250 due to the one set of bleachers and one set of restrooms on that side.

- Concessions
- All workers will have the appropriate PPE’s
- Workers will be responsible for one specific action for the entire event. (No crossover)
- Adjustments to order lines and pick-up lines are being made.
*Outside concession stand lines have room to be extended by several yards if needed
- All items will be pre-packaged or singularly prepared for the customer.
- We will make several announcements to alleviate the pressure during intermissions.

North Miami has a new lunch system! One of the new features is the ability to accept an on-line free/reduced lunch application. This application is used to qualify for textbook rental assistance.

The link for the application is available on our website in the Parent tab. It has to be completed in one setting and cannot be save and restarted.

If you are unsure if your family qualifies please complete the application and our Food Service Director will contact you.

Paper applications are also available in the office of each of our buildings.

post_text:
Good afternoon, Seniors. Thank you for making the trip in this week to return your laptops and other school items. We continue to follow Miami County Health Department Guidance in our plans for summer.

As you are aware, we are planning Senior Awards and Commencement to be held on July 12th, at 2:00. At this point, we anticipate providing 5 tickets to each graduate for guests. If the reopening of the state goes well, we may be able to provide more. Administration will be hand delivering official invitations along with the tickets in the first couple weeks of June.

Also, we are looking into other plans including a Senior Bonfire and Graduation Practice. These events will be scheduled during the week of July 6th, and details will be forthcoming.

Lastly, we still have a tentative prom date of August 1st. We will be able to confirm plans for prom when the state's reopening reaches "stage four."

Any parents who are interested in helping with events should call the school (765-985-2931, Extension 5255), and leave a message expressing that interest in helping with Mr. Storm.
text:
Good afternoon, Seniors. Thank you for making the trip in this week to return your laptops and other school items. We continue to follow Miami County Health Department Guidance in our plans for summer.

As you are aware, we are planning Senior Awards and Commencement to be held on July 12th, at 2:00. At this point, we anticipate providing 5 tickets to each graduate for guests. If the reopening of the state goes well, we may be able to provide more. Administration will be hand delivering official invitations along with the tickets in the first couple weeks of June.

Also, we are looking into other plans including a Senior Bonfire and Graduation Practice. These events will be scheduled during the week of July 6th, and details will be forthcoming.

Lastly, we still have a tentative prom date of August 1st. We will be able to confirm plans for prom when the state's reopening reaches "stage four."

Any parents who are interested in helping with events should call the school (765-985-2931, Extension 5255), and leave a message expressing that interest in helping with Mr. Storm.

Attention MS/HS Students:

Tomorrow and Thursday we'll have the building open from 10:00-6:00 for students to return their laptops and retrieve belongings. During your visit, plan to do the following:
1.) Sanitize and sign-in upon entering.
2.) Sign up for WiFi Assistance though United Way, as needed.
3.) Pick up Driver's Education information, if enrolled.
4.) Label your laptop with your name, place in location designated by grade level.
5.) Turn in other school resources, such as textbooks, library books, or otherwise.
6.) Retrieve belongings, such as items left in your locker, and art projects.
7.) Erase your name from the sign in list upon departure.

Seniors should turn in chargers as well, but all other students can keep chargers at home. Please remove any stickers from your laptop before turning it in. For those who are assigned summer school (or those who will need laptops for other programs), they will be reimaged and ready for pick up by June 1st.

post_text:
Class of 2020:

1. Graduation Requirements have been adjusted, including the Graduation Qualifying Exam and Graduation Pathways. The expectation is for you to finish each of your enrolled courses. Not finishing a course would lead to an “incomplete” on the final transcript and may prohibit you from meeting graduation requirements. Final GPA’s and Class Rank will be based on the first 7 semesters.

2. Jostens orders can be picked up Thursday, April 16th, in front of MS/HS from 3:00-6:00. Also, please prepare a short video (30 seconds or less) of a message for your classmates. Graduation and other significant events will be rescheduled with guidance and approval from the state.

Rather than bumming about what you’re missing, focus on the opportunities and experiences you have enjoyed over your high school career, as well as those that lie ahead. We are here to help, so let us know if you have any questions.

National FFA Organization
February 27 at 6:58 PM ·

Wednesday, Allison B. received her first FFA jacket.

It was a milestone moment for her. And it was a milestone moment for everyone who loves FFA. Allison's jacket was the 10,000th FFA jacket donated through Give the Gift of Blue – a program that makes it possible to gift jackets to FFA members that began in 2014.

Currently, only 4 out of 10 FFA members own a jacket. You can make a difference in that number right now at www.FFA.org/give

Thank you North Miami FFA and North Miami Community Schools for helping us celebrate during National FFA Week!

post_text:
Greetings all! Please help spread the word!

The North Miami Alumni Band AND Color Guard Night will be Fri. Jan. 31st! This is a double header home basketball game. Our Alumni Band/Guard will play/perform at both games. Call time is 5pm. We will rehearse through the music before the games. This is open to ANY North Miami Alumni OR any Band/Guard Alumni from other schools as well. We are ONE BIG MUSIC FAMILY, so the more the merrier! The NM FFA will also be having their All you can eat Chicken/Fish Fry dinner this night, which starts at 4:30pm. I am pretty certain tickets are $10/person. Feel free to come out and help support them as well!

During this game, the NM Music program will be holding a silent auction of some old full band picture frames from a variety of years, selling Marching Shako's (hats WITHOUT PLUMES) for a $5 donation, and just having a wonderful Music Family Time together reliving old memories.

Please help spread the word! I would love for this to end up being a HUGE event for our school!!!
-Sarah McBride
